# Transport BID Portal - Project Conventions

## Stack
- **Backend**: ASP.NET Core (.NET 10), SQL Server LocalDB, Entity Framework Core
- **Frontend**: Vanilla JS + HTML5 + CSS3 (SPA-like with sidebar navigation)
- **Auth**: JWT with Role-Based Access Control (Shipper, Carrier, Admin)
- **Excel**: ClosedXML for template export/import
- **PDF**: QuestPDF for report generation
- **Charts**: Chart.js for data visualization

## Architecture
- Controllers in `Controllers/` — thin, delegate to services
- Domain entities in `Domain/` — EF Core models with `[MaxLength]`
- DTOs/records in `Contracts/Dtos.cs`
- Services in `Services/` — business logic, interface + implementation
- Single `AppDbContext` with seed data for demo users
- `Program.cs` registers all DI services

## Key Patterns
- Use primary constructors for DI injection
- Use `CancellationToken ct` on all async endpoints
- Use `DeleteBehavior.Restrict` for FK relationships that could cascade
- Use `HasPrecision(18, 2)` for monetary decimals
- CEP lookups use in-memory cache + SQL fallback via `ICepService`
- Freight calculation uses OpenRouteService API via `IFreightService`

## Frontend
- All navigation via `navigateTo(pageId)` — sections have `class="page-section" data-page="xxx"`
- Sidebar items created dynamically in `sidebarBuild(role)`
- Use `authHeaders()` for all API calls (includes JWT + CorrelationId)
- Never use `innerHTML +=` for DOM manipulation (destroys event listeners)
